According to my tax form, I turned a sweet profit by selling the horses I “acquired” in Turkmenistan.

Turkmen cuisine, like most Central Asian cuisine, is most famous for its parties. When you invite someone over for “tea” (soy chay), you know to expect enough food for 30 extra guests, many of which you will end up serving because you are a welcome guest in their house. For us to eat a fish or fresh meat-based meal, we would have to go out of our way – very far – to find a restaurant. Going to a restaurant was reserved for birthdays and achievement dinners or for when visiting relatives living in Ashgabat. We cooked delicious meals at home with local produce when we were there for dinner. Thousand Days’ Mustard is one of my favourite Turkmen recipes.

Around the world, the term “istan” refers to the land of something, like “jamaica” refers to the land of jamaica flowers. Central Asia, unknown to people with European or American origins
